 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record the use of an individual product to make a connection.</p>
<example><p> Pipe FW_102 and pipe FW_103 are both individual
products. The pipefitting PF_99 that joins pipe FW_102 and pipe FW_103 is also
an individual product.</p>
<p>The relationship between the pipefitting PF_99 and the connection between
pipes FW_102 and FW_103, that indicates the pipefitting is used to make the
connection, is an Involvement_of_individual_product_in_connection.</p>
</example>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
<li><p>a relationship between:</p>
<ul>
<li>a connection between individual products; and</li>
<li> an individual product,</li>
</ul>
<p>that indicates the individual product is used to make the connection.</p>
</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
<li><p>class of involvement of product in connection;</p>
<note number="1">Class of involvement of product in connection is within
the scope of the
<module_ref linkend="class_of_involvement_of_product_in_connection:1_scope">Class_of_involvement_of_product_in_connection</module_ref> application module.</note>
</li>
<li><p>classification of a involvement of product in connection;</p>
<note number="2">Classification of an involvement of product in
connection is within the scope of the
<module_ref linkend="product_structure_and_classification:1_scope">Product_structure_and_classification</module_ref> application module.</note>
</li>
<li><p>connection between individual products.</p>
<note number="3">Connections between individual products are within the
scope of the <module_ref linkend="connection_of_individual_product:1_scope">Connection_of_individual_product</module_ref> application module.</note>
</li>
 </outscope>

